    "title": "Wrong block mined time in testnet",
    "body": "### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [X] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Current behaviour\n\nCurrently, all block mined time in testnet could be about 1 hour earlier than current time.\r\n \r\n<img width=\"1285\" alt=\"testnet\" src=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/assets/51077262/4df52a40-7b45-4a4d-8535-f1564e9a8705\">\r\nlink: https://blockexplorer.one/bitcoin/testnet\r\n\r\nTimestamp in UpdateTip is wrong. \r\n```\r\n│ app-generic 2024-05-16T06:57:48Z Saw new header hash=000000000000000ba2e0919b2ab27d045c41bd4e6115667c2ef453e405db01da height=2815696             │\r\n│ app-generic 2024-05-16T06:57:48Z [net] Saw new cmpctblock header hash=000000000000000ba2e0919b2ab27d045c41bd4e6115667c2ef453e405db01da peer=11   │\r\n│ app-generic 2024-05-16T06:57:48Z UpdateTip: new best=000000000000000ba2e0919b2ab27d045c41bd4e6115667c2ef453e405db01da height=2815696 version=0x2 │\r\n│ 235c000 log2_work=75.782354 tx=135221647 date='2024-05-16T07:51:39Z' progress=1.000000 cache=209.9MiB(1241814txo)\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like wrong stamp is derived from getblocktemplate response? 'curtime' and 'mintime' is always quite earlier than current time.  \n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nBlock mined time should be close to current time. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nExecute `bitcoin-cli getblocktemplate '{\"rules\": [\"segwit\"]}'`, check 'curtime' and 'mintime'. \n\n### Relevant log output\n\n_No response_\n\n### How did you obtain Bitcoin Core\n\nPackage manager\n\n### What version of Bitcoin Core are you using?\n\nv25.0\n\n### Operating system and version\n\nUbuntu18\n\n### Machine specifications\n\n_No response_",
